        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 2 at 5:15PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 514 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a thunderstorm over
Orange, or near Shelton. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and brief heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Milford, Orange, and West Haven.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
